title: I’m Always Here
body:
Anon requested: Can you do an imagine where tony is a father figure to the reader and she hits her breaking point and finally trusts tony enough to tell him that she self harms? He just helps her and make sure she knows Nat she’s loved and that he’ll do anything to help.

Warnings: self-harm, depression, mental illness, trigger warning

Author’s note: thank you for the request! Keep on sending them in!

Tony had always been there for you. When your parents died when you were thirteen, he took you under his wing and has always treated you as his own. He always made sure you were taken care of and that you were happy. He never would’ve guessed that you were depressed, mainly because you always put on a good show for the world.

It was a particularly rough night for you. You woke up with a start in the middle of the night due to your recurring nightmares. You hadn’t had nightmares since your parents died, but they were back, and they were back with a vengeance. You always dreamt the same thing: the way your parents died and you weren’t able to save them. This had been going on for months now and you always resorted to the same coping mechanism–self harm. It definitely wasn’t the best, you knew that, but it was all you knew how to do. You had been doing it ever since your parents died. You got out of bed and went into your bathroom. You opened the cupboard by the mirror and took out a prescription bottle. You opened it and let the blade you hid in it fall into your hand. You sat on the edge of the bathtub and raised your shorts. You always cut where people wouldn’t see so no one would question you–that’s how you’ve gotten away with it all these years. A few tears fell down your cheeks as you lifted the blade and held it to the skin on your thigh. You glided the blade across your thigh and you didn’t even flinch when you did. You had gotten used to the pain by now. You did this a few more times until you were as satisfied as you knew you were going to get.

You woke up the next morning with a sharp pain in your leg. You had bled all over your bed sheets.

“Shit,” you muttered and hobbled over to your bathroom to clean your leg. You cleaned all the blood off your leg and just sat on the bathroom floor staring at the wall. All of a sudden you broke down. You cried and cried and cried until you didn’t have any tears left. You were tired. You were tired of constantly hurting yourself and you were tired of hiding it from everyone, most importantly Tony. You eventually got up off the floor and walked back into your bedroom. You stripped the bed of the bloody sheets and replaced them with fresh, clean ones. You gathered the bloody sheets and made your way down to the laundry room to bleach them.

“Good morning, sunshine,” you heard behind you. You froze in your place and kept walking. Tony came up to you and grabbed your shoulder, spinning you around.

“What’s wrong, honey?” he asked. The second you met his eyes, you broke down again. Tony saw the bloody sheets and looked at you with a questioning look.

“Do we need to go to the store?” he asked. He thought you were on your period. You shook your head, still crying and dropped the sheets to the floor. Tony had no idea what was going on and he was starting to freak out.

“Y/N, what’s going on? This isn’t funny,” he said sternly.

“There’s something I’ve been keeping from you,” you said shakily. Tony gave you another quizzical look. You lifted your shorts to show him the fresh cuts. Among that, Tony saw your thigh littered with old and new scars. It was worse than anything he’s ever seen.

“Y/N,” he whispered, trailing off. Tears immediately started forming in his eyes. “Why did you never tell me sooner?”

“I don’t know,” you muttered. You didn’t want to tell him it was because you didn’t trust him enough yet. But now you did. And you needed help. Badly. You continued to cry and Tony softly shushed you, wiping away your tears.

“It’s okay. I’m going to get you through this, okay? I love you so much and I’m not going to let you go through this alone, okay? You have me, and you know for a fact you have the whole team,” said Tony, matter of factly. You didn’t know what to say, so you just nodded in response.

“Now those cuts look really deep, so let’s go to the lab and Bruce will stitch you up. He won’t tell anyone. I promise. This is between you and me and whoever else you tell,” continued Tony. Once again, you nodded. Tony picked up the bloody sheets off the floor and ushered you to Bruce’s lab.

“Always know that I’m always here for you no matter what. I would go to the ends of the earth for you, and I need you to know that. We’re gonna get you through this. And no matter what, I’ll always love you,” finished Tony. You nodded again, a small smile on your face. You really owed that man the world.
